text: With eager hands, we plant the seeds, In fertile soil, they take their creeds, The sun shines bright, its warmth imparts, A nourishing embrace, it opens hearts.
The sprouts emerge, a tender green, Their leaves unfold, a wondrous sheen, They stretch and grow, their vigor keen, Drinking in the sun's pure beam.
Their roots delve deep, they thrive and twine, A living tapestry, intertwined, Their colors burst, a vibrant hue, A symphony of life, anew.
The fruit ripens, a juicy prize, Sweet nectar flows, a tasteful surprise, The earthy scent, a fragrant delight, A feast for senses, morning, noon, and night.
The sun's rays dance, a shimmering haze, A nourishing grace, it never fades, The cycle complete, a living spell, Feeding the sun, our souls as well.
